column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind Blowing Upstream
column14: FAIR STREAMPRO MEASUREMENT UNDER ICE UPSTREAM OF GAUGE - NORMAL MEASUREMENT SECTION IN USE BY CITY OF IQALUIT FOR WATER CONSUMPTION DURING STAGE OF EMERGENCY RESERVOIR CONTAMINATION. MEASUREMENT HAS 16 VALID PANELS AND 1@16% TOTAL FLOW DUE TO IRREGULAR FLOW DISTRIBUTION. TIME CONSTRAINTS AND EQUIPMENT ISSUES PERVENTED ADDITIONAL PANELS BEING ADDED AFTER THE FACT. COMPLETE ICE COVER AT GAUGE POOL, WATER LEVEL TAKEN <2m FROM ORIFICE, VISIBLE BENEATH ICE. HEAVY FOOT TRAFFIC AND AUGER HOLES IN AREA DUE TO IQALUIT WATER EMERGENCY. ***MEASUREMENT IN AQUARIUS SHOULD NOT BE CHECKED FOR USE IN RATING DEVELOPMENT. NO RELATIONSHIP UNDER ICE**** OPERATING TECH WILL COMPUTE FINAL 2021 WINTER FLOW ATER FAST TRACK IS COMPLETE Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Snow and some slush on shore but channel below gauge still looks clear. B conditions possible but not expected. Some thin ice on off shore in front of gauge.
column14: -Wade just upstream from parking lot , right above where the flat water turns to riffles. -0.6 method used the whole transect as time did not allow 0.2/0.8 method.   Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of 0.018 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 3.005 -While taking cut for DWL, tripped on loop of cable. It was the CS451 twisted and frozen into the edge ice with armour missing. Broke it free and laid it flat to hopefully prevent damage when ice moves. -Change in HG readings is due to this as I either moved the block a bit or the release of the cable being twisted allowed for an improved pressure differential. HG not reset. -SRC of 0.018 for MGH based on last few readings before adjustment being 3.007. Mid-section
